PRESS DIGEST - Chinese newspapers - Aug 18 . Following is a summary of major Chinese political and business stories in leading newspapers , prepared by Reuters in Beijing . Reuters has not checked the stories and does not guarantee their accuracy . Telephone : ( 8610 ) 6532 - 1921 . Fax : ( 8610 ) 6532 - 4978 . - - - - PEOPLE ' S DAILY - China delays launch date of Philippine satellite . - Number of domestic and foreign tourists visiting the Three Gorges increases sharply . - Construction approved for 1 , 350 megawatt power station in southwestern Yunnan province . - Output value of township enterprises in central China ' s Hunan Province surges 49 . 5 percent year - on - year in the first half . - - - - FINANCIAL NEWS - Assets of Everbright Bank of China reach 51 . 1 billion yuan at end - June - China allocates 6 . 915 billion yuan at end - June for resettlement of people living near the Three Gorges dam project . - Sales of Haier group hit 4 . 813 billion yuan in the first half , up 68 . 5 percent year - on - year - - - - CHINA SECURITIES - Dong Fureng , vice - chairman of the Finance and Economic Committee of the National People ' s Congress , says centralisation of stock markets will reduce interference by local authorities and other irregularities . - - - - ECONOMIC DAILY - China ' s private sector employed about 25 million people at end - June , up 1 . 7 million from the end of 1996 . - Fixed asset investment up 10 . 5 percent year - on - year in the first seven months of this year . - Editorial says China needs more world - class conglomerates to boost its competitiveness . - - - - PEOPLE ' S DAILY OVERSEAS EDITION - China can export about 600 , 000 tonnes of zinc this year , and domestic zinc prices seen rising to 115 , 000 yuan per tonne in 1997 . - - - - CHINA WOMEN ' S NEWS - China uncovered 39 , 015 drug cases between April and June , arresting 55 , 211 people . - - - - LIBERATION ARMY DAILY - Gymnastics champion Li Xiaoshuang will not attend world gymnastics tournament because of foot injury - - - - XINHUA DAILY TELEGRAPH - China ' s rural economy has been booming since the 14th National Congress of the Communist Party of China in 1992 . - State survey says cash income of farmers rose 3 . 3 percent year - on - year in the first half of 1997 . - - - - FARMER ' S DAILY - Corn output up by 200 , 000 tonnes this year from 1996 - - - - MARKET DAILY - China distillery Qinchi group to form $ 6 . 0 million joint venture with Italian firm to produce wine . - - - - CHINA BUSINESS TIMES - China sees gold output at 122 - 130 tonnes for 1997 . - - - - ECONOMIC INFORMATION DAILY - Daya Bay nuclear power station generates 6 . 774 billion kilowatt hours of electricity at end - July . - China ' s car prices fall between one percent and 8 . 1 percent in the first half of this year . - - - - CHINA DAILY - Transport authorities improving poor maintenance of fast - growing highway network . 
